althy growing earnings, and that <em>one=C2=A0</em>quarter is terrible but =
investors are willing to look past it. If you have to take one big write-do=
wn this quarter, you might as well hunt around for every other possible wri=
te-down, because if you take them all this quarter they sort of don=E2=80=
=99t count, whereas if you wait until next quarter they=E2=80=99ll hurt.</p=
